Attica Department Store, located in
the center of the Greek capital, posted a 15 percent revenue
decline in the first five months of the year, daily  Kathimerini 
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Konstantinos Labropoulos.  Sales at the mall fell to 27.5 million euros ($35 million),
while revenue at the Golden Hall in the northern Athens suburb
of Marousi declined 6.9 percent to 13.6 million euros, the
Athens-based newspaper said, citing Labropoulos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
